**📋 Ultimate Step-by-Step Guide: How to Copy Clipboard Text from Android and Instantly Paste It on Windows 11 Using PairDrop (No App Needed)**

---

### 🔧 What You’ll Need:

* One Android device (with internet access)
* One Windows 11 PC or laptop
* Both connected to the **same Wi-Fi** or **mobile hotspot**
* **No app installation required** – just use a modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)

---

### 🚀 Step-by-Step Tutorial: Copy from Android → Paste on Windows Using PairDrop

#### 1️⃣ Open **PairDrop** on Both Devices

* On **Android**, open Chrome (or your browser of choice) and go to:

  > [https://pairdrop.net](https://pairdrop.net)
* On your **Windows 11 PC**, open the same site in any browser:

  > [https://pairdrop.net](https://pairdrop.net)

> 📌 Tip: Keep both tabs open and active during the session.

---

#### 2️⃣ Allow the Devices to Discover Each Other

* Wait a few seconds.
* Your **Android screen** will show your Windows device (e.g., `DESKTOP-1234`) and vice versa.

---

#### 3️⃣ Copy the Text You Want to Send on Android

* Long-press any text on Android (from a message, website, etc.).
* Tap **Copy** to place it in the clipboard.

---

#### 4️⃣ Tap Your Windows Device Icon on Android

* In the PairDrop tab on Android, tap your **PC's icon**.
* Then select the **“Send Text”** option.

---

#### 5️⃣ Paste the Text from Clipboard

* Tap the input field.
* **Long-press** and choose **Paste** to insert the copied text.
* Tap **Send**.

---

#### 6️⃣ Receive the Text on Windows

* On your **Windows 11 PC**, you’ll instantly see a pop-up from PairDrop with the text.
* Click the **Copy** button on that pop-up.

✅ The text is now in your **Windows clipboard**. You can paste it anywhere (Ctrl+V)!

---

### 🔄 Summary

| Action                   | On Android | On Windows |
| ------------------------ | ---------- | ---------- |
| Open PairDrop            | ✔️         | ✔️         |
| Copy text                | ✔️         | –          |
| Send via "Send Text"     | ✔️         | –          |
| Receive and click "Copy" | –          | ✔️         |
| Paste (Ctrl+V)           | –          | ✔️         |

---

### 💡 Bonus Tip:

If you want full **automatic clipboard syncing** (without manually pasting/sending), check out:

* **KDE Connect**
* **Clipto**
* **Scrcpy + ADB clipboard tools** (advanced)

Want a guide for those too? Just ask!
